DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Urine Free Kappa Light Chain Measurement
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of urine, the fluid that is excreted by the kidneys for Kappa immunoglobulin light chain, one of the two light chain proteins that are part of the protein complex found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma and is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine._Number that is expressed as maximum of eight characters in length, with three decimal places.
